Ptyxis is a modern terminal emulator built for the container era,
designed to seamlessly integrate with GNOME desktop environments.

Key Features:
- Modern GNOME interface built with GTK4 and libadwaita
- Dynamic theming with extensive color palette support
- Smart process tracking (sudo, SSH sessions)
- Advanced tab management with live previews
- Customizable keyboard shortcuts and user profiles
- High-performance rendering with GPU acceleration
- Terminal inspector for debugging
- Encrypted scrollback buffers for enhanced privacy

OpenBSD-specific notes:
This port has been adapted to work with OpenBSD 7.7 using libadwaita 1.6
and VTE 0.78. Container integration features (Podman, Toolbox, Distrobox)
are not available on OpenBSD as they require Linux-specific functionality.
The core terminal emulation features work fully.
